HEADWORD: Catafalque
<hw>Cat"a*falque`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., fr. It.
<ets>catafalco</ets>, scaffold, funeral canopy; of uncertain origin; cf.
Sp. <ets>catafalso</ets>, <ets>cadahalso</ets>, <ets>cadalso</ets>, Pr.
<ets>casafalc</ets>, OF. <ets>chafaut</ets>. Cf.
<er>Scaffold</er>.]</ety> <def>A temporary structure sometimes used in
the funeral solemnities of eminent persons, for the public exhibition of
the remains, or their conveyance to the place of burial.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Catagmatic</ent>⟦br⟧
